An All Progressives Congress stalwart in Niger State, Dr. Aminu Mohammed Baka have aspirants who were not picked as consensus candidates at the just concluded national convention of the party to take it in good faith. He urged them to join the new party leadership to work towards retaining the presidential seat and other positions in the forthcoming general elections. Dr. Baka in a press statement in Minna, said, “I commend every aspirant for accepting in good faith the decision of President, Muhammadu Buhari for consensus candidates to be chosen, he stated. The APC Chieftain explained that, in recent times, conducting a successful convention devoid of rancour and dissenting opinions has become a herculean task, hence, the effort put in by the Caretaker and Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee, especially Governor Mai Mala Buni and Niger State Governor, Abubakar Sani Bello who stood in for him when preparation for the convention was in top gear should be commended. ” I want to congratulate our great party the APC on the just concluded successful convention. I also congratulate the chairman, His Excellency Abdullahi Adamu and the leadership of the party. I have full confidence that under the leadership of our chairman, I am confident that you will provide the needed leadership to turn this party around. I have no doubt that you will work with dedicated and qualified Nigerians to preserve our party and continue to lead by example,” Dr. Baka said. The state party chieftain urged all party members to continue to work for the interest of the party as there was no winners or losers during the convention.